scene.message:
Maki: So this is your hideout!{nl}
You're not getting away{nl}
this time!{waitkey}{ret}

Aki: Nyaah!{nl}
You can't go any further!{nl}
Well, except for that one{nl}
in the forest, but...{waitkey}{clearbox}He hasn't got the guts,{nl}
so nobody can get in the{nl}
way of Aki and Papa!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Hey, Nanjo!{nl}
Don't just stand there{nl}
spacing out. Got any ideas?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Without a key that{nl}
fits this half-moon hollow,{nl}
we won't get in.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: From the way she{nl}
spoke, there must be{nl}
someone else who holds it.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: The forest...{nl}
that must be the one on{nl}
the west side.{waitkey}It used to be a lovely{nl}
flower garden, but now{nl}
they call it the Lost Forest.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Then let's go back.{nl}
We need to find whoever{nl}
holds the key.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Urgh~ We're going back?{nl}
How about the leader stays{nl}
here on lookout? No good?{waitkey}Oh, all right then.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Whaaat~{nl}
We came all this way and{nl}
now we go back? The worst!!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Nothing for it, let's{nl}
go back. Gotta find this{nl}
'him' the brat mentioned.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: Back when the Lost{nl}
Forest was a garden, a girl{nl}
named Mai played there...{waitkey}Maybe she's the one{nl}
they mean.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: That brat's gotta be{nl}
Kandori's kid for sure.{nl}
They're just alike in how{nl}
irritating they are.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: ...{wait_fr:60}{ctl0f:1},{nl}
that child's behavior...{nl}
doesn't something bother you?{waitkey}I feel like we're being{nl}
made to dance.{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Still, that child...{nl}
Kandori must mean so{nl}
much to her...{wait_fr:94}{nl}
A little enviable...{waitkey}{clearbox}Oh, I'm sorry, that was{nl}
a strange thing to say...{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: I get it, I get it.{nl}
I'll go back properly.{nl}
You'd be lost without your{nl}
leader, after all.{waitkey}{ret}

Ayase: Hey, {ctl0f:1}~{nl}
carry me piggyback~{waitkey}C'mon, you get to feel{nl}
Ayase's warmth, don't you?{nl}
Right?{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: ...{wait_fr:60}So he's up{nl}
above here...{nl}
You won't escape me.{waitkey}Wash your neck and wait{nl}
for me, bastard...{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Hold on, Reiji.{nl}
This isn't something you{nl}
can just smash.{waitkey}{clearbox}When it comes to Kandori,{nl}
your whole look changes, man.{nl}
I won't pry too deep, but...{waitkey}don't try to carry it{nl}
all alone.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: ...Kido,{nl}
Inaba's right.{nl}
We're comrades, aren't we?{waitkey}{ret}

Reiji: ...{wait_fr:60}I've no interest{nl}
in chumming up with you.{nl}
Comrades? Makes me sick.{waitkey}{clearbox}Especially you, Inaba...{nl}
Just looking at you{nl}
turns my stomach.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: It's fine, Sonomura.{nl}
Stomach-turning or not,{nl}
for now we've got no choice{nl}
but to head back together.{waitkey}{clearbox}Our goal's the same.{nl}
Let's get going then, {ctl0f:1}.{waitkey}{ret}

Maki: I just don't get boys.{nl}
Inaba, you seem to{nl}
actually like Kido.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: What?{nl}
'Have I got a fever'?{nl}
What's that supposed to mean?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: For Inaba to take that{nl}
much and stay quiet...{wait_fr:92}{nl}
Heh...{waitkey}{clearbox}He probably catches the{nl}
same scent. He's like{nl}
a beast, after all.{waitkey}{ret}
